    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-23T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="569"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2361/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-23T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 23, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2021. Embassy’s 1731, October 26, 6 a.m.<note n="94" xml:id="d569fn94">See
                        footnote 78, <ref target="#pg_716">p. 716</ref>.</note> Arrangements have
                    been made for Dr. Waldron to proceed by air to visit the interned bomber crews
                    and he hopes to proceed within a few days.</p>
                <p>A letter signed by Maj. Richard D. Salter<note n="95" xml:id="d569fn95">U.S. Army
                        Air Corps; leader of the group of bomber air crews interned at Yangi
                        Yul.</note> dated October 11 was received by the Embassy on November 25 [<hi
                        rend="italic">20</hi>]. He states all personnel are well and are receiving
                    excellent care but that they are very anxious to talk with an American
                    representative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
